## Findings

### 🟡 Major: Invalid auto-promoted candidates are silently deleted from the queue

In `trackShortTermMatches()`, once `match_count >= AUTO_PROMOTE_MATCHES`, the item is not pushed to `remaining`, even if `validateCandidate(item)` rejects it:

```ts
if ((item.match_count ?? 0) >= AUTO_PROMOTE_MATCHES) {
  const candidate = validateCandidate(item);
  if (candidate) {
    writeAcceptedMemory(...)
  }
  changed = true;
} else {
  remaining.push(item);
}
```

